ENTRY            E2805   20260226   20260227   20260227       E155
SUBENT        E2805001   20260226   20260227   20260227       E155
BIB                 12         34
TITLE      Competition between mass-symmetric and asymmetric
           fission modes in 258Md produced in the 4He + 254Es
           reaction
AUTHOR     (K.Nishio, K.Hirose, H.Makii, R.Orlandi, K.R.Kean,
            K.Tsukada, A.Toyoshima, M.Asai, T.K.Sato, N.M.Chiera,
            T.Tomitsuka, K.Tokoi, R.Yanagihara, H.Suzuki,
            Y.Nagame, K.Okada, A.N.Andreyev, T.Tanaka, K.Morimoto,
            S.Ishizaki, M.Okubayashi, Y.Miyamoto, S.Tanaka,
            S.Takagi, Y.Aritomo, S.Kubono, N.Iwasa, M.Egeta,
            S.Sakaguchi, S.Matsunaga, Y.Ishibashi,
            K.P.Rykaczewski, R.A.Boll, J.Z.Ezold, L.K.Felker,
            J.B.Roberto)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNJAE,2JPNTIT,2JPNNII,2JPNOSA,2UK YRK,2JPNIPC,
           2JPNKYU,2JPNKNK,2JPNTOH,1USAORL)
           (2JPNJPN) Graduate School of Science and Engineering,
                     Ibaraki University, Ibaraki
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,111,044609,2025)
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
           - Target-thickness is 0.00032 mg/cm2.
           - Backing is nickel.
           - Backing-thickness is 0.27 mg/cm2.
METHOD     Double velocity method
           (TOF,COINC)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2JPNJAE)
ANALYSIS   As the average fragment velocity does not change after
           prompt neutron emission from the fragment, the method
           gives preneutron emission fragment mass and TKE.
DETECTOR   (MWPC,MCPLT)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) background subtraction
REL-REF    (O,23624001,K.Nishio+,J,PR/C,111,044609,2025)
           250Cf(sf) data compiled separately
HISTORY    (20250526C) K.Suzuki
           (20251212R) Received by e-mail from Dr. K. Nishio.
ENDBIB              34
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
 5.
ENDCOMMON            3
